contributions.title: Natural High
contributions.notes:
Produced by Mike Vernon for the Crystal Jukebox. Strings and Horns arranged and conducted by Pip Williams
Recording Engineer: Tony Reale. Recorded at The Village Recorder, West Los Angeles, California, July 1972.
Bloodstone are: Charles Love - Vocal, guitar; Willis Draffen Jr. - Vocal, guitar; Roger Durham - Vocal, percussion; Harry Williams - Vocal, percussion; Charles McCormick - Vocal, bass guitar; Melvin Webb - Drums, conga, timbales
With additional help from:
Eddie Summers - Vocals, drums, vibes, piano, conga on "That's The Way We Make Our Music"
Hense Powell - Piano, electric piano, organ; Gordon Dewitte - Organ; Mike Vernon - Glockenspiel, castanets, tubular bells; Gene Cipriano - Cor Anglais; Arthur N. Maebe - French horn; Richard L. Mackey - French horn; Jacqueline Lustgarten - Cello; Raymond L. Kelley - Cello; Nathan Kaproff - Viola; Dan Neufeld - Viola; Violins: Carla Spencer, Erno Neufeld (leader), Paul C. Shure, Samuel Boghossian

Our special thanks go to Carol Kathi, Dick, Harry Wilkins and all the electronic boffins at Village Recorder, with an extra special word for a great engineer; and let us not forget two fine roadies, John and Mick (who also "plays" wind chimes). The Crystal Jukebox gives special thanks to: Lloyd (again), Lord H. and Friends, and all the good people of England.
